ATLANTA, GA: Even when bad things happen, life is better when you do it together! That's the motto of bonded brothers-from-different-mothers Wexley and Widgeon. These 10 year old boys recently lost their human mom who, sadly, passed away. Wexley and Widgeon were loved and cared for, and it shows today. They've spent their life together and they must be adopted together. It takes a special person to adopt two older puppies, but we also know there are a lot of special people out there. 
PLEASE SHARE to help us find Wexley and Widgeon's special someone!! Orphan Annie Rescue wrote, "Meet Wexley and Widgeon! They are a bonded pair of #Malteses and they are both 10 years old. Their human mommy passed away. While they are not litter mates, they are the best of friends. They are in good health, VERY cuddly, and extremely loving and sweet.

Widgeon is a bit bigger than Wexley and is the more playful of the two. Wexley is a the precious guy you see with his tongue sticking out, as he has no teeth! They use pee pads and belly bands due to our former mom's health issues, she could not regularly take them outside. They are good with dogs and cats, but love people most of all! 
Their adoption fee is sponsored. They are neutered, up to date on shots, heartworm testing, senior bloodwork and microchipping. They are available for adoption along the east coast." To adopt Wexley and Widgeon, please email orphanannierescue@gmail.com with any questions! ❤️ #seniordog #bonded #brothers #bestfriends #atlanta #georgia #adoptdontshop #adoptdontbreed

People often ask me how I was able to grow my Instagram account from zero to 100K in two years. The short answer: A background in social media, passion for Atlanta and a little bit of luck! The long answer.. well it's called a long answer or a reason! 😜

This workshop is perfect for bloggers, small business owners and anyone looking to learn about one of today's most popular social media channels. If you're not using Instagram, you're missing out on an incredible way to connect with your audience!
How to Up Your Insta Game with ATL Bucket List is on Wednesday, June 7 from 7-9 pm at @switchyards. Tickets can be purchased by clicking the link in @yoursocialteam's bio.
